# Theme-Aware Bento Grid Animation

The current animation is optimized for dark mode and becomes invisible in light mode due to the white core disappearing against the white background. This plan implements theme-aware visual logic.

## Proposed Changes

### Component: [BorderBeam.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/components/ui/border-beam.tsx)

#### [MODIFY] [BorderBeam.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/components/ui/border-beam.tsx)
- **Dynamic Core Stroke:** 
    - In **Dark Mode**: Maintain the high-contrast `white` core.
    - In **Light Mode**: Switch the core to `var(--primary)` (Deep Blue) to provide a sharp, visible leading edge against the white glass.
- **Contrast Boosting:**
    - Increase the `opacity` of the "Aura" and "Bloom" layers in light mode. This ensures the soft glow has enough saturation to overcome the ambient brightness of the light theme.
- **Tailwind Integration:** Use Tailwind regular and `dark:` classes to handle the color transitions seamlessly without needing complex theme-detection hooks.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- **Light Mode Check:** Verify the beam is sharply visible as a Blue/Cyan streak on white boxes.
- **Dark Mode Check:** Verify the beam remains a stunning White/Cyan streak on black boxes.
- **Transition Check:** Ensure the switch between themes is smooth.
